  Title: Hardcoded Web Admin Credentials
  Affected artifact (path/URL): First-boot-Diagnosis-Info/config_all/config/config_a.xml:360
  Short description: Firmware ships with the web UI set to admin/admin, stored as an unsalted MD5 hash and even documented in a comment.
  Vulnerable code snippet (≤40 lines):

  360		<Device>
  374			<!-- passwd:admin -->
  375			<WebLoginPasswd>21232f297a57a5a743894a0e4a801fc3</WebLoginPasswd>
  377			<WebLoginUserName>admin</WebLoginUserName>
  378			<WebLoginPasswd20>0X]&0D]]05</WebLoginPasswd20>

  Repro steps:
  sed -n '360,378p' First-boot-Diagnosis-Info/config_all/config/config_a.xml
  echo -n admin | md5sum
  PoC?: Yes – the MD5 digest 21232f297a57a5a743894a0e4a801fc3 matches the stored hash, confirming the credential.
  Remediation: Provision unique admin credentials per device and store only modern salted password hashes (e.g. bcrypt/argon2).
  Severity (CVSS 3.1 AV:N/AC:L/PR:N/UI:N/S:U/C:H/I:H/A:L): 8.8 High
  Tools & versions used: sed (BSD), md5sum (Darwin) 1.0, bsdtar 3.5.3

  Title: Weak WiFiSoapAP Key
  Affected artifact (path/URL): First-boot-Diagnosis-Info/config_all/config/config_a.xml:65
  Short description: Embedded hot-spot and fallback AP both use the trivial key 12345678 with AuthMode 0, enabling quick wireless compromise.
  Vulnerable code snippet (≤40 lines):

  65		<WiFiSoapAP>
  69			<SSID></SSID>
  70			<Key>12345678</Key>
  73			<AP>
  74				<SSID></SSID>
  75				<Key>12345678</Key>
  76				<AuthMode>0</AuthMode>
  77				<EncrypType>0</EncrypType>

  Repro steps:
  sed -n '64,79p' First-boot-Diagnosis-Info/config_all/config/config_a.xml
  PoC?: Yes – configuration shows the shipped WiFi credentials.
  Remediation: Disable the SOAP AP by default or enforce random, high-entropy WPA2/WPA3 credentials and non-null SSID during provisioning.
  Severity (CVSS 3.1 AV:A/AC:L/PR:N/UI:N/S:U/C:H/I:H/A:N): 7.4 High
  Tools & versions used: sed (BSD)

  Title: Hardcoded PTZ/BoxDome admin/12345 Credentials
